Package banking

package banking
  • Class
    Description
    Account
    The Account class holds the information regarding a bank account The account number, Profile object of the holder, and the balance are held in each account
    AccountDatabase
    The AccountDatabase class holds the information regarding all the bank accounts.
    AccountNode
    AccountNode class used for the Archive to store closed Accounts in a linked list implementation.
    AccountNumber
    The AccountNumber class holds the Account Number.
    AccountType
    The AccountType class holds the information regarding all the different types of accounts that can be opened at the bank.
    Activity
    Represents a banking activity such as a deposit or withdrawal.
    Archive
    Archive will hold Accounts that have been closed
    Branch
    The Branch enum class holds the information regarding all the different types of Branch locations.
    Campus
    The Campus enum class represents different campus locations.
    CertificateDeposit
    Represents a Certificate Deposit account, which is a time-bound savings account with fixed term durations and varying interest rates based on the term selected.
    Checking
    The Checking class represents a type of bank account with a specific interest rate, fee structure, and conditions related to balance thresholds.
    CollegeChecking
    CollegeChecking is a specialized type of Checking account tailored for college students.
    MoneyMarket
    Represents a Money Market account, which is a specialized type of Savings account that offers distinct features such as higher interest rates, specific fee structures, and withdrawal limitations.
    Profile
    The Profile class holds the information regarding a person who holds the bank account, Full name and date of birth are part of their profile.
    RunProject2
    RunProject2 is a class that calls the TransactionManager which will manage transactions.
    Savings
    Extends the account class
    TransactionManager
    Transaction Manager class that reads in transactions from the command line.
